		<td><b>NES Dual Port RAM Interface</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Just did a writeup on an NES project I've been working on. A dual port RAM replacement for the console that allows you read/write memory live via serial. Routed out a couple of extra pins soldered directly to RESET &amp; NMI to remote reset / frame step for debugging.<br /><br /><img src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-IqOi_WHTuM8/U2atiuJS6HI/AAAAAAAAAhQ/u7VvqT3svGo/s1600/unnamed+(2).jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Pulling live data from Blades of Steel to create a scoreboard / trigger a relay on a goal:<br /><a href="https://vine.co/v/M6WzFBXeX1e" class="postlink">https://vine.co/v/M6WzFBXeX1e</a><br /><br />Triggering a relay on firing in Contra:<br /><a href="https://vine.co/v/M6WZlFjdJ69" class="postlink">https://vine.co/v/M6WZlFjdJ69</a><br /><br />A live hex editor inspired by FCEUX:<br /><a href="https://vine.co/v/M6qEpOvMzQz" class="postlink">https://vine.co/v/M6qEpOvMzQz</a><br /><br />Frame Stepping:<br /><a href="https://vine.co/v/M6qLIIKUeT6" class="postlink">https://vine.co/v/M6qLIIKUeT6</a><br /><br /><a href="http://www.batslyadams.com" class="postlink">http://www.batslyadams.com</a> if you want more technical details!

		

